<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Zero on 12-07-2000 09:13 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Okay, you apparently misread my post...

1)  I never said the location of the key wasn't known.  We can get the key all we damn well please but if the program goes public we're banned.

2)  I meant it would be possible for *US* to write a program which stopped Everquest, or any program that was flagged for that matter, from looking in any memory block other than it's own and system resources (logging all attempts made to view them).

3)  See number 2, since my post isn't really numbered and you felt so incensed as to not include quotes I think that's what you were referring to which was just a misunderstanding.

4) EQvault and the rest will never post a program that breaks the EULA, but this program wont break the EULA.  It does nothing but log attempts made by a program to access memory outside of it's own block.

5)  I wasn't aware they banned EQMacro users.  The reason they got away with it is because there's an "Ends justify means" mentality.  If there is a possibilty that for every SEQ user they ban they're also banning a regular user there is a good chance that they wont do it, Public Opinion would kill them.

6)  I'm sure quite a few people would be interested in knowing wether or not Verant is breaking their word, if they use it we are safe.  They don't even have to know they are helping us.

then my reply to your second 1) is: As far as I can tell the only thing which is currently stopping us from writing a program that will grab info from memory and send it over to the linux box is the fact that it would be detectable by Verant scanning memory (which would be what the program would thwart).

As for the remark about Banning without justification.  Yes they can do it, and they have done it on a small scale.  They can't afford to do it on a large scale, and PR is already barely balanced.  LtM would have a field day and they will lose major points with Sony.

Finally, are you such a peon and is your life so pathetic that you have to go onto the internet and flame others on a message board to satisfy your Sociopathic needs?</TEXTAREA>
